pullRequest.body:
This PR adds the `SpecialFunctions/Log/ENNRealLog.lean` file where we define `log` as an extension of the logarithm of a positive real to the extended nonnegative reals `‚Ñù‚â•0‚àû`. The function takes values in the extended reals `EReal`, with `log 0 = ‚ä•` and `log ‚ä§ = ‚ä§`.

Co-authored with @D-Thomine.

Are you planning to also add `exp` in the other direction? (I'm asking because the order iso version and the homeomorphism version would love to have a simp lemma saying that, when you apply their symm, it coincides with exp). If yes in a near future, then everything is perfect. If not, can you add a todo about this at the end of the file-level comment?
I just have a few comments, but globally it looks good! I think it would be good to also add lemmas about `(ENNReal.log x).toReal`, my guess is that it would come up in practice quite a bit.

```suggestion

We define `log` as an extension of the logarithm of a positive real
```

Can you mention the namespaces in the references to statements in docstrings? for instance, here it should be
```suggestion
- `ENNReal.log`: The extension of the real logarithm to `‚Ñù‚â•0‚àû`.
```
I guess the last one is `log_rpow`?
Yes, sorry.

```suggestion
the identities `log (x * y) = log x + log y` and `log (x ^ y) = y * log x`
```
Done.

```suggestion
`log (x * y) = log x + log y` unconditional.
-/
```
end docstrings with one single hyphen, not two. Also, if you started the docstring with hyphens on their own line, the same should apply to the end of the docstring.
Done. Thanks.

```suggestion
theorem log_of_nnreal {x : NNReal} (h : x ‚â† 0) :
```
Also, could you use `‚Ñù‚â•0` for `NNReal` everywhere (type with `\nnr...`).

This statement is weird, because you are going through the map to reals and then to ennreals. It would be more natural to formulate it through the coercion from nnreal to ennreal (and then you could mark it as simp).
Done. Thanks.

```suggestion
/-- `log` as a homeomorphism. -/
```
The h at the beginning of "homeomorphism" is pronounced, so it starts with a consonant.

```suggestion
theorem log_continuous : Continuous log := Homeomorph.continuous log_Homeomorph
```

```suggestion
noncomputable def log_orderIso : ‚Ñù‚â•0‚àû ‚âÉo EReal :=
```
Also, can you add a simp lemma saying that `log_orderIso x = log x`?

```suggestion
- `log_mul_add`, `log_pow`, `log_rpow`: `log` satisfy
the identities `log (x * y) = log x + log y` and `log (x ^ y) = y * log x`
(with either `y ‚àà ‚Ñï` or `y ‚àà ‚Ñù`).
```
The file should just be named `ENNReal`, because we're already in the `Log` subdirectory.

```suggestion
theorem log_ofReal {x : NNReal} (h : x ‚â† 0) :
    log (ENNReal.ofReal x) = Real.log x := by simp [log, h]
```
or maybe something like `log_ofReal_nnreal`, or just `log_nnreal` (I know the lowercase `nnreal` technically violates the naming convention, but from a quick doc search, this seems to be an exception we've settled on.)

```suggestion
theorem log_of_nnreal {x : ‚Ñù‚â•0} (h : x ‚â† 0) :
    log (x : ‚Ñù‚â•0‚àû) = Real.log x := by simp [log, h]
```

Hi @dupuisf, I've directly pushed your suggested commit but it seems to throw an error.

Unfortunately I am traveling at the moment so I can't access my computer.

I reverted it to: 

```lean
theorem log_of_nnreal {x : NNReal} (h : x ‚â† 0) :
    log (x : ENNReal) = Real.log x := by simp [log, h]
```
The version by Fr√©d√©ric is definitely better. You should use it, and open whatever is needed to make the notation work.
Ok, I‚Äôm going to do it as soon as I can.
Right, you need to put `open scoped NNReal` somewhere for this notation to work.

Ops, you're right. I'm going to add it later today. 

Thanks.
Done.

```suggestion
- Define `exp` on `EReal` and prove its basic properties.
```
Done.
Could you add a simp lemma saying that `log_orderIso x = log x`?
Done

```suggestion
noncomputable def log_homeomorph : ‚Ñù‚â•0‚àû ‚âÉ‚Çú EReal := OrderIso.toHomeomorph log_orderIso
```
Also, could you add a simp lemma saying that `log_homeomorph x = log x`?
Done.
